                            <comment id="406018" author="adilger" created="Fri, 1 Mar 2024 22:55:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Shaun, I just noticed in a test run that this is being set and then cleared for &lt;b&gt;every subtest run&lt;/b&gt;, across all of the servers. This would be far better to do only once per test session to avoid adding extra SSH overhead to every subtest that is run.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If libcfs_debug_raw_pointers was made a module parameter then it could automatically be set by the test framework on module load, and no need to even set the parameter at runtime. Alternately, or additionally, it would be possible for test-framework.sh to use:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;     do_facet mgs &quot;$LCTL set_param -P debug_raw_pointers=Y&quot;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;when the filesystem is formatted so that it is always set at mount time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
